PN,43102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1774469469
OL,3,CCampaigners protest redevelopment of
OL,4,Cformer zoo site
OL,6,FIt's the third time that campaigners
OL,7,Fhave staged a protest outside of the
OL,8,FAcorn offices in Bristol, calling on
OL,9,Fthe zoo's trustees to re-think their
OL,10,Fdecision to give the company control
OL,11,Fof what they say is "such an important
OL,12,Fsite".
OL,14,FTom Jones, founder of Save Bristol Zoo
OL,15,FGardens said "Just because Bristol Zoo
OL,16,Fclosed three years ago, it's still
OL,17,Fthere and the society still own it.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,432,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1774469469
OL,3,CCampaigners protest redevelopment of
OL,4,Cformer zoo site
OL,6,F"We believe it's an unacceptable
OL,7,Fcourse of action for the zoo to take
OL,8,Fand we're calling on the trustees to
OL,9,Fhalt the sale.
OL,11,FHe added: "It's madness, it's
OL,12,Fecological vandalism and right now I
OL,13,Fthink the trustees are defending the
OL,14,Findefensible. "
OL,16,FAnother member of the group, Carrie
OL,17,FSage, said "What we will have is a
OL,18,Fbeautiful site destroyed with
OL,19,Fconcrete, a road, car parking, trees
OL,20,Fcut down and half built. An absolute
OL,21,Ftragedy for Bristol."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,432,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1774469469
OL,3,CCampaigners protest redevelopment of
OL,4,Cformer zoo site
OL,6,FIn a statement, Acorn said: "We will
OL,7,Fbe completing the sale and developing
OL,8,Fthis prestigious scheme.
OL,10,F"To reaffirm, we are committed to
OL,11,Fcreating a new community space,
OL,12,Fopening the gardens for free public
OL,13,Faccess, and providing a mix of
OL,14,Faffordable and open-market homes.
OL,16,F"We welcome open discussion with the
OL,17,Flocal community on this project. We
OL,18,Fhave met with local councillors and
OL,19,Fhad a meeting arranged for today with
OL,20,Fthe Save Bristol Gardens Alliance,
OL,21,Fwhich they rescheduled.
OL,26,@xD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,432,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1774469469
OL,3,CCampaigners protest redevelopment of
OL,4,Cformer zoo site
OL,6,F"We are therefore really disappointed
OL,7,Fwith the decision to continue to
OL,8,Fdemonstrate outside our offices. We
OL,9,Fwill always welcome open dialogue, but
OL,10,Fthis has to be in a constructive
OL,11,Fforum."
OL,13,FThe Chief Executive of the Bristol
OL,14,FZoological Society Dr Justin Morris
OL,15,Fhas stood by the decision made by the
OL,16,Ftrustees saying: "Of course I
OL,17,Funderstand why people are attached to
OL,18,Fthe site but the gardens will remain
OL,19,Fand they will become open and
OL,20,Faccessible for free for the first time
OL,21,Fin the site's history.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@GO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
